==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tamboura
<hw>Tam*bour"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A stringed musical instrument resembling a lute
but lacking frets, with a small round body and a long neck, used to
produce an accompaniment for singing; -- called also
<altname>tambur</altname>, <altname>tambour</altname>, and
<altname>tampur</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>tambura</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tambourin</ent>⟦br⟧
